This paper discusses the task of automatic keyphrase extraction, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of keyphrase extraction models, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper mentions the use of scientific articles, which may involve deep learning techniques, making cs.DL (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
